	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64534845">Dont put a device rated for a 110 V connection into a 220 V connection. Ohms law says V/I=R. For the same R a larger V will pull a larger current (I). Now the heat generated is proportional to the power ( I*I*R) so a large current will burn your wires down as they are not rated for that current and heat.</div>
	</div>

